# Button Controlled LED

This project demonstrates how to control an LED using a push button with an Arduino/ESP32. Pressing the button changes the LED state, introducing the basics of digital input and output in embedded systems.

## Components Used
- Arduino/ESP32
- Push Button
- LED
- Resistor(s)
- Breadboard & Jumper Wires

## Features
- Reads button input using a digital pin.
- Turns the LED ON/OFF based on button state.
- Demonstrates basic GPIO programming.
